also, note about quest:

there's 3 types of VARIABLES:

VARIABLES:
-&gt; (1) Variables: local VARIABLES
-&gt; (2) Attributes: global VARIABLES (as long as the Object it is &quot;attached to&quot; exists, of course)
-&gt; (3) Parameters: for Functions and Commands, hopefully you already understand about these, as they're a pain to try to explain, lol

you did change the 'return (tryme)' to 'tryme()', right?

it's in your 'else', see below:

&lt;function name=&quot;tryme&quot; type=&quot;boolean&quot;&gt;
     msg (&quot;Try me?&quot;)
    get input {
      if (result = &quot;no&quot;) {
        msg (&quot; Okay im sad&quot;)
        return (false)
      }
      else if (result = &quot;yes&quot;) {
        msg (&quot;YaY&quot;)
        return (true)
      }
      else {
        msg (&quot;What?&quot;)
        [b:9xcjm8io][size=150:9xcjm8io]return (tryme)[/size:9xcjm8io][/b:9xcjm8io]
      }
    }
  &lt;/function&gt;

it should look like this:

[code:9xcjm8io]&lt;function name=&quot;tryme&quot; type=&quot;boolean&quot;&gt;
     msg (&quot;Try me?&quot;)
    get input {
      if (result = &quot;no&quot;) {
        msg (&quot; Okay im sad&quot;)
        return (false)
      }
      else if (result = &quot;yes&quot;) {
        msg (&quot;YaY&quot;)
        return (true)
      }
      else {
        msg (&quot;What?&quot;)
        tryme()
      }
    }
  &lt;/function&gt;[/code:9xcjm8io]

-------

and your:

myvariable = tryme

must be:

myvariable = tryme ()

as you need the parenthesis, to tell quest that the 'tryme' is a Function, and not an Object nor a VARIABLE.

ah, if you're using 'get input' or 'show menu', it's very very difficult to get a loop (such as recursion) to work, as the loop occurs while the first 'get input' or 'show menu' is waiting for input or selection by you, and thus another 'get input' and 'show menu' runs, which causes a crash, as you can't have two of them running at the same time.

---------

quest uses its own langauge: quest's code design structure is similar to Python, but its scripting code is similar to C++ or Java.

Also, for the 'creation' tag blocks, in code, that uses 'XML', XML is similar to a browser language like HTML

